## 11. Availability-badge semantics for orphans

Depends on §9. Assuming Resolution A (the join model):

### 11.1 Decision: tombstones

- `iptv_title_link` gains `removed_at TEXT NULL` column (migration
  `0003_link_tombstones.sql`).
- `iptvSync.ts` no longer deletes link rows for missing upstream items.
  Instead, sets `removed_at = <now>`.
- `tagIptvAvailability` filters `WHERE removed_at IS NULL`.
- Hard delete after 30 days of `removed_at IS NOT NULL` — gives the
  upstream catalog time to re-add an item without losing watch history
  via the cascade.

### 11.2 Decision: live channels in `available_on`

- **Excluded.** Live channels don't map to TMDB titles cleanly (a "TNT"
  channel doesn't have a single TMDB id). The recommender returns
  TMDB-keyed items; live channels would clutter the badge with
  meaningless entries.
- **Exception future-work**: if M6 introduces "this movie is airing on
  channel X at 8pm" via EPG matching, that's a new badge kind
  (`available_on: ['iptv-live']` or a separate `airing_soon` field) —
  not a stretching of the current badge.

### 11.3 Decision: orphans with no TMDB match

- IPTV VOD/series without `tmdb_id`: they have no rows in
  `iptv_title_link` and no rows in any `titles` table. They are
  invisible to the recommender. **Visible only in the IPTV tab's own
  browse views.** That's correct behaviour; no badge work needed.

---

## 12. Server / app version compatibility gates

Required before any TestFlight build. Locked.

### 12.1 Decision: `/api/version` endpoint

Shape per §7.2 above. Public (no auth). Stable contract from day one.

### 12.2 Decision: app-side gates

- App first-connect:
  - If `server.api_versions` does not include the app's required version:
    show "Please update your server" screen.
  - If server returns `426 Upgrade Required`: show "Please update via
    App Store" screen.
- Min-server-version constant in EmeraldKit, bumped per app release.
- Min-client-version constant in Hono `env.ts` (`MIN_CLIENT_VERSION`),
  defaults to "0.0.0".

### 12.3 Decision: `server_id` introduction

- Generated on first boot: `INSERT INTO server_state(key, value) VALUES('server_id', <uuid_v4>)`.
- Returned by `/api/version`.
- Embedded in device tokens (§3.2). On token validation, server checks
  `token.server_id == own server_id` → rejects tokens from another
  server. (Edge case: user restored a backup from a different server
  install. Honest 401, app re-pairs.)

### 12.4 Decision: response when too old

- Server too old for app: `426 { "required_version": "<min app version>", "current_version": "<server version>", "reason": "server_too_old_for_client" }`.
- App too old for server: `426 { "required_version": "<min server version>", "current_version": "<app version>", "reason": "client_too_old_for_server" }`.

---

## 13. CI contract gates

Required to ship before M2 starts.

### 13.1 Test vectors

- `tests/vectors/stream-token-canonical.json`: list of {claims_input,
  canonical_bytes_hex, hmac_hex_with_test_key}. Asserted by Hono test
  suite **and** Rust `emerald-contracts` integration test.
- `tests/vectors/device-token-claims.json`: list of {claims, expected
  shape conformance}. Asserted by Hono + Swift EmeraldKit test target
  (when M2 starts).
- `tests/vectors/sub-namespace.json`: list of {input, expected
  parse output | rejection reason}. Asserted by Hono + Rust + Swift.

### 13.2 Migration tests

- Hono: existing migrator boot smoke test, extended to assert
  `schema_migrations` table populated and checksums match.
- Recommender: same for `exchange.db`.
- **Skip-version test**: spin up empty DB, apply migrations 1→N
  sequentially, assert schema matches a golden snapshot.
  `tests/golden/iptv-schema-v<N>.sql` + `tests/golden/exchange-schema-v<N>.sql`.

### 13.3 Reproducible no-IPTV build

The "App Store insurance" build (strategy doc § App Store hardening)
must build green from CI on every commit, not just at release time.
- New `IPTV_DISABLED` compile flag in Hono (M1.5 work).
- New CI job `build:no-iptv` that builds Hono with the flag, runs the
  test suite, asserts no `/api/iptv/*` routes are mounted.
- For M2 onward: Xcode build setting `IPTV_DISABLED=YES` strips the
  IPTV browse tabs; same CI gate.

### 13.4 ffmpeg sidecar version validation

- `server/services/ffmpeg.ts` (M1.5 placeholder — does not exist yet)
  exposes a `ffprobe -version` check at boot.
- Boots fail loud if ffmpeg < 6.0 (HLS LL features) or missing entirely.
- M4 transcoder boot extends this with encoder enumeration.

### 13.5 Version-skew tests

- Hono integration test: server vN, client claims vN+1 → 426.
- Hono integration test: server vN, client claims vN-1 (compatible) → 200.
- Run on every commit.

