## 15. Telemetry posture [USER'S CALL]

Strategy doc §11 proposed self-hosted Glitchtip as the default. This
contract doc defers.

**Decision needed:**
- **Sentry SaaS**: best UX, $26/mo for Team plan; commits user metadata
  to Sentry's privacy policy. Requires App Store privacy nutrition
  labels listing "Crash Data" + "Diagnostics" + the Sentry processor.
- **Self-hosted Glitchtip**: privacy-clean (data stays on the NAS), more
  ops cost. Same App Store labels (still "Crash Data" + "Diagnostics"),
  but the data processor disclosure is "us, the developer".
- **Local-only**: log to file, no upload. Privacy-cleanest. Useless
  for debugging crashes from users who can't share log bundles. App
  Store labels: "Data Not Collected".

**Decision impact downstream:**
- Determines App Store privacy nutrition label content — required at
  submission, not amendable per release without re-review.
- Determines whether `emerald-contracts` exposes a `tracing` integration
  shape.
- Determines `/api/admin/diagnostics` (strategy doc §11) endpoint scope.

