## 16. M1 deltas to apply before M2

These are the breaking changes the contract requires, applied while M1
is still the only consumer. Each is a small PR.

| # | Delta | File(s) | Effort |
|---|---|---|---|
| D1 | Switch `signStreamToken` to canonical JSON (alphabetical-sorted keys, `v: 1`, renamed `k`/`rid`/short claims) | `server/services/iptvStreamToken.ts`, all call sites in `server/routes/iptv.ts` | 2-3h |
| D2 | Introduce `STREAM_TOKEN_SECRET` env, fallback to `SESSION_SECRET` with warn log | `server/env.ts`, `iptvStreamToken.ts` | 1h |
| D3 | Add `jti` to stream tokens + bloom-cache replay defence | `iptvStreamToken.ts`, new `server/services/tokenReplayCache.ts` | 4h |
| D4 | Normalise `SessionKind` vs `StreamKind` enums; document mapping | `iptvConcurrency.ts`, `iptvStreamToken.ts` | 1h |
| D5 | Add `server_id` generation at boot, store in `server_state` table | `server/migrations/0001_*.sql` (new general migration outside iptv), `server/index.ts` | 2h |
| D6 | Implement `GET /api/version` per §7.2 / §12 | new `server/routes/version.ts` | 2h |
| D7 | Identity namespace prefix migration + parser guard | new `server/migrations/iptv/0002_namespace_sub.sql`, `server/session.ts`, `server/middleware/auth.ts`, all sub-using code | 4h |
| D8 | Add `schema_migrations` table convention everywhere it isn't (verify recommender + iptv migrators populate it) | `server/services/migrator.ts`, `recommender/app/db.py` (or wherever the Python migrator lives) | 3h |
| D9 | Resolve recommender data-model contradiction per §9 user decision | varies | 1-3 days |
| D10 | Add CI contract gates per §13 | `.github/workflows/*.yml`, new test files | 1 day |
| D11 | Tombstone columns on `iptv_title_link` per §11.1 (only if §9 = A) | new migration, `iptvSync.ts`, `suggestions.ts` | 3h |

**Total estimate:** ~1 week of work for D1–D8, +1-3 days for D9, +1 day
for D10. The strategy doc's 1-2 week estimate holds.

D1 + D2 + D7 are the deltas that **must** apply before any TestFlight
build mints a device token. After that point, changing them forces
re-pairs.

